<h1>@HI{{ne}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> <strong>@HI{{ne}}</strong>.
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{ne}}</strong> is a sentence ending particle. It can be used to:
<ul>
<li> indicate emotion or feelings of admiration
<li> indicate agreement with the other person
<li> soften a request
<li> request confirmation
<li> indicate a mild assertion of opinion
<li> indicate a mild assertion
</ul>
</p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{kireina@KJ{{flower}}<strong>ne</strong>.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      What a pretty flower.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{book^hit}}nisoudesu<strong>ne</strong>.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      That's so true.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{invariably}}zu@KJ{{hand^paper}}okudasai<strong>ne</strong>.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Be sure to write a letter to me.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{meadow^rice*field}}san,@KJ{{now^day^come}}ruto@KJ{{say}}ttandesu<strong>ne</strong>.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Harada said he'd be coming today, right?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{soudesuka<strong>ne</strong>.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      You think so?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{private}}ha@KJ{{north^sea^road-way}}no@KJ{{direction}}ga@KJ{{cold}}ito@KJ{{think}}undesukedo<strong>ne</strong>.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I would think that Hokkaido is colder.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

